<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870812-0038 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Mcdonnell Douglas Corp.</HL><DD> 08/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD </IN><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Corp., St. Louis, said it received an order for one of its Delta II rockets, valued at about $50 million, from the London-based International Maritime Satellite Organization.    The aerospace concern said it will build and launch the rocket, which will carry a communications satellite for International Maritime, a 48-nation cooperative that operates a satellite system for maritime mobile communications. McDonnell Douglas said it expects to launch the rocket in the fourth quarter of 1989. </TEXT></DOC>